.TH "vmw_validation_res_switch_backup" 9 "vmw_validation_res_switch_backup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_res_switch_backup \- Register a backup MOB switch during validation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_validation_res_switch_backup
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "void *val_private "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *vbo "  ","
.BI "unsigned long backup_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
The validation context.
.IP "val_private" 12
The additional meta-data pointer returned when the
resource was registered with the validation context. Used to identify
the resource.
.IP "vbo" 12
The new backup buffer object MOB. This buffer object needs to have
already been registered with the validation context.
.IP "backup_offset" 12
Offset into the new backup MOB.
